OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1776125001
OL,3,CRetail sales 'tepid' as Middle East
OL,4,Cconflict raises consumer caution
OL,6,FAn early Easter gave the month's food
OL,7,Fsales an artificial boost to an
OL,8,Fincrease of 6.8%, and inflation was
OL,9,Falso a factor, driving up overall
OL,10,Ftotal UK retail sales to 3.6% higher
OL,11,Fthan a year ago, above the 12-month
OL,12,Faverage of 2.6%.
OL,14,FIn an indicator of lowered consumer
OL,15,Fconfidence, online non-food sales
OL,16,Fincreased by just 0.1%, well below the
OL,17,Fyear average of 1%.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1776125001
OL,3,CRetail sales 'tepid' as Middle East
OL,4,Cconflict raises consumer caution
OL,6,FDemand was robust for computers, toys,
OL,7,Fand homeware, but clothing and
OL,8,Ffootwear continued to struggle, while
OL,9,Fthe disruption to international travel
OL,10,Fcaused by uncertainty in the Middle
OL,11,FEast also hit sales of travel-related
OL,12,Fgoods.
OL,14,FBRC chief executive Helen Dickinson
OL,15,Fsaid: "An early Easter provided a much-
OL,16,Fneeded boost to food sales as families
OL,17,Fcame together over the long weekend.
OL,26,@wD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1776125001
OL,3,CRetail sales 'tepid' as Middle East
OL,4,Cconflict raises consumer caution
OL,6,F"Retailers hope that the Middle East
OL,7,Fceasefire will bring lasting
OL,8,Fstability, but the outlook remains
OL,9,Funcertain.
OL,11,F"Damage to supply chains has already
OL,12,Fbeen done, and rising costs ` from
OL,13,Fshipping and fertiliser to insurance
OL,14,Fand commodities ` are piling yet more
OL,15,Fpressure on to already stretched
OL,16,Fretailers.
OL,18,F"Government must act decisively and
OL,19,Fboldly now to curb inflation by
OL,20,Fdelaying domestic policies that would
OL,21,Fpush prices even higher for shoppers."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUzD@AOU}D@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1776125001
OL,3,CRetail sales 'tepid' as Middle East
OL,4,Cconflict raises consumer caution
OL,6,FLinda Ellett, UK head of consumer,
OL,7,Fretail and leisure at KPMG, said:
OL,8,F"Food and drink continue to drive
OL,9,Fmonthly retail sales growth, with
OL,10,Finflation a key factor.
OL,12,F"Non-food sales growth remains tepid,
OL,13,Fgrowing at under 1% so far this year,
OL,14,Fas consumer spending caution is
OL,15,Fheightened by the current and
OL,16,Fpotential impact of the Middle East
OL,17,Fconflict."
OL,26,@pD@AOUtD@AOUyD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
